text:
PARIS—There is no evidence of foul play or violence in Anthony Bourdain’s death in France, a French prosecutor said Saturday.

The famed chef, writer and host of the CNN series “Parts Unknown” killed himself Friday in a luxury hotel in the ancient village of Kaysersberg, Christian de Rocquigny, the prosecutor of Colmar in France’s eastern Alsace region, told the Associated Press in a phone interview.
